Internet Assigned Number Authority (http://www.iana.org/) is responsible for the assignement of Private Enterprise Numbers (PENs).  They are primarily used as object identifiers for LDAP and X.500 directories in locally-defined schema and in the Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMP) and related standards. 
For LDAP and X.500, the usage is in the form of 1.3.6.1.4.1.X where the number assigned to the enterprise replaces X.